notes.name: Course Note
notes.content:
Timetable Instructions

For more information, please contact foundation.program@utoronto.ca or 416-946-5146.

Delivery Instructions

Some aspects of the course are delivered on line at the scheduled time and students are required to attend online at the same time. Students need an internet connection and access to the course website (Quercus) and the ability to use online tools made available by the university, such as Office 365 and BB Collaborate. Students may require access to a webcam and microphone.

cmCourseInfo.description: Surveys the development of human societies from their origins to the present using examples from across the world. Topics may include the environment, cultural development and interaction, the creation and nature of belief systems, political, economic and social structures, gender relations, and the relationship between global patterns and local developments. Enrolment is restricted to students registered in the International Foundation Program. Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
cmCourseInfo.title: Themes in World History

Some aspects of the course are delivered online at the scheduled time (e.g., tutorials, lectures) and students are required to attend online at the same time. Lecture recordings will also be made available for access outside of class time. Students need an internet connection and access to the course website (Quercus) and the ability to use online tools made available by the university, such as Office 365. Students may require access to a webcam and microphone.
